[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":121},["Reactive",2],{"content-query-f35m5zxZo3":3},{"_path":4,"_dir":5,"_draft":6,"_partial":6,"_locale":7,"_empty":6,"title":8,"description":7,"body":9,"_type":116,"_id":117,"_source":118,"_file":119,"_extension":120},"/blog/en/the_plus_register_of_vim_is_useful","en",false,"","The '+' register of Vim is useful",{"type":10,"children":11,"toc":111},"root",[12,20,27,33,39,44],{"type":13,"tag":14,"props":15,"children":17},"element","h1",{"id":16},"the-register-of-vim-is-useful",[18],{"type":19,"value":8},"text",{"type":13,"tag":21,"props":22,"children":24},"h2",{"id":23},"background",[25],{"type":19,"value":26},"Background",{"type":13,"tag":28,"props":29,"children":30},"p",{},[31],{"type":19,"value":32},"Vim is a powerful editor as far as we know even as to be somewhat kind of standard for programmers. However, there is one problem usually confuses noobs: copying codes from Vim interface to another interface in the system is hard as vim have different inner clipboard being different from the system clipboard.",{"type":13,"tag":21,"props":34,"children":36},{"id":35},"basic-info-of-vim-register",[37],{"type":19,"value":38},"Basic info of Vim register",{"type":13,"tag":28,"props":40,"children":41},{},[42],{"type":19,"value":43},"There are lots of register of Vim which stores code copied or clipped to be pasted somewhere.\nThe usage of registers is easy.",{"type":13,"tag":45,"props":46,"children":47},"ul",{},[48,81],{"type":13,"tag":49,"props":50,"children":51},"li",{},[52,58,60,65,67,72,74,79],{"type":13,"tag":53,"props":54,"children":55},"code-inline",{},[56],{"type":19,"value":57},"\"",{"type":19,"value":59}," Register is the default register. To use it, just add the prefix ",{"type":13,"tag":53,"props":61,"children":62},{},[63],{"type":19,"value":64},"\"\"",{"type":19,"value":66}," or nothing. For instance, if you hope to put the code in the line where your cursor at into the \"register, push ",{"type":13,"tag":53,"props":68,"children":69},{},[70],{"type":19,"value":71},":",{"type":19,"value":73}," in normal mode or visual mode, and input ",{"type":13,"tag":53,"props":75,"children":76},{},[77],{"type":19,"value":78},"\"\"yy",{"type":19,"value":80},", then the code in that line is yanked in the \"register.",{"type":13,"tag":49,"props":82,"children":83},{},[84,89,91,96,98,102,104,109],{"type":13,"tag":53,"props":85,"children":86},{},[87],{"type":19,"value":88},"+",{"type":19,"value":90}," Register is the most useful register as it corresponds to the system clipboard. The usage of it, adding the prefix ",{"type":13,"tag":53,"props":92,"children":93},{},[94],{"type":19,"value":95},"\"+",{"type":19,"value":97}," before your instructions, is the same as ",{"type":13,"tag":53,"props":99,"children":100},{},[101],{"type":19,"value":57},{"type":19,"value":103}," register.\nFor example: in order to copy the code in the line your cursor at, type ",{"type":13,"tag":53,"props":105,"children":106},{},[107],{"type":19,"value":108},":\"+yy",{"type":19,"value":110}," in normal mode.",{"title":7,"searchDepth":112,"depth":112,"links":113},2,[114,115],{"id":23,"depth":112,"text":26},{"id":35,"depth":112,"text":38},"markdown","content:blog:en:39.The_plus_register_of_Vim_is_useful.md","content","blog/en/39.The_plus_register_of_Vim_is_useful.md","md",1696766335755]